<title>USA: Soundview urges &quot;aggressive&quot; view on tech stocks.</title>
<headline>Soundview urges &quot;aggressive&quot; view on tech stocks.</headline>
<dateline>STAMFORD, Conn. 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Soundview Financial Group president and market strategist James Townsend on Monday reiterated a short-term &quot;overweight&quot; position on the technology sector and urged a &quot;more aggressive&quot; view toward the technology sector.</p>
<p>&quot;While the broad market remains a complicating factor, we believe it is time to take a more aggressive posture toward the technology sector,&quot; Townsend said in a research note.  </p>
<p>Townsend said he sees a 15 to 20 percent rise in Soundview's Technology Index by the end of May.</p>
<p>Townsend cited several stocks that have &quot;better than average&quot; upside potential,&quot; including: Adobe Systems Inc; Adtran Inc ; Autodesk Inc ; BMC Software Inc ; DSC Communications Corp ; and Intel Corp.</p>
